Project: Hartford – (Feb - 25 to June – 25)

GitHub Enterprise to Git Cloud Migration

Roles and Responsibilities:


Planning and Strategy:

•	Develop a comprehensive migration plan, including timelines, milestones, and risk assessments.

•	Identify and document all repositories, users, and access controls in the current GitHub Enterprise environment.

•	Define the target state in Git Cloud, including repository structure, access controls, and integration points.

Migration Execution:

•	Execute the migration of repositories from GitHub Enterprise to Git Cloud, ensuring minimal downtime and data integrity.

•	Use migration tools and scripts to automate the transfer of repositories, issues, pull requests, and other metadata.

•	Validate the successful migration of each repository and its associated data.


Coordination and Communication:

•	Coordinate with development teams to ensure a smooth transition and address any concerns or issues.

•	Communicate the migration plan, progress, and any changes to all stakeholders.

•	Provide regular updates and reports on the migration status.

Best Practices Implementation:

•	Implement best practices for repository management, including naming conventions, branching strategies, and access controls.

•	Ensure compliance with security and governance policies in the new Git Cloud environment.

•	Set up and configure necessary integrations with CI/CD pipelines, issue tracking systems, and other tools.

Post-Migration Activities:

•	Monitor the new Git Cloud environment for any issues or performance concerns.

•	Gather feedback from users and stakeholders to identify areas for improvement.


